The paper proposes the use of deep learning approaches, specifically the Deep Deterministic Policy Gradient (DDPG) algorithm, for optimizing traffic light timing in urban areas. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with the coordination of multiple agents (traffic lights) in a network, which falls under the Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper may also involve computer vision techniques for processing traffic data, which could place it in the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category.
